	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 29th 12:09 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>To a person in a high end guild, the issue of aggro isn't an problem.&nbsp;&nbsp;They have better weapons, Blade of Carnage and Hategiver for examples and they also have aggro adding spells.  With that out of the way, you look at usefullness.  How I see it, is that 13/20 isn't bad and the ability to slow attacks while soloing becomes a great asset.  With that in mind, I would use this to solo and switch it out after it procs to one of my better daggers.  I don't have to worry about others needing this dagger as an upgrade, because I know they all have better.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
