	   <tr><td colspan=2>Seeing all these post claiming this and that I am actually wondering how many of 'em that has ever been down to Variki and made a go at this weap.<br><br>Lets try and keep this board sober and stick to the info that is true and useable for our fellow champions of Norrath.<br><br>My guild went to DN to have a go at this mofo. First... How did the person entering the post "I doubt" ever come up with the story 'bout a dragon doing 1k AE spell? And nobody ever contradicted him. That leads me to think that most ppl posting on this subject knows squat.<br>Second...Stating that he can be taken with just 6 peeps makes me laugh. Aye it might even happen once in a life if all 6 had the luckiest day in their life. Apart from that....don't even count on it.<br><br>Variki is a ratboss in DN. He has like 30k hp (roughly estimated give or take 10k) and gates when low on hp.<br>To get to him ye need to follow the left wall when entering DN. Go through the big door that seperates the spiderarea with the combined spider and rat area. Whatch out for traps and don't use illusions. If doing so ye will be DT'ed. Keep following left wall and ye will get to a path that slightly goes downwards. This will take ye to a rat and bat area. Here roams Variki.<br><br>Single pulling him is extremely difficult since he holds a large court of rats around him. All rats are like lvl 53 or better. Hits in the upper 180 tops (if I recall correctly).<br>Spawnrate for roamers art fast so it is VERY easy to get adds.<br><br>We used the wrong tactic (first time there is my only excuse for our messup).<br><br>We pulled him and a few adds. Disposed the adds rather easy with like one or 2 casualties. All went on him and we had him to like 10% hp when he gated and came back with reinforcemnts. Again we killed the adds fairly easy (few casualties this time too) and started to pound on him again. When he was low casters started nuking but he still managed to gate and again he brought back adds. Now ppl started going LD in a steady stream and casters went LOM. This is when the bad times started to happen. I was one of the last ones standing when I went LD too. When logging on I was dead. Some weren't but since most had spawned again they got disposed off easily. 30 peeps or so dead. All between 51 and 60. Few with epics and most peeps in the upper 50's.<br>No way this mofo is a walk in the park!<br>The CR was trivial and took some time. Lots of coffins used.<br><br>Buffed up for second go. Went down there easily. Started to pull some mobs away from other peeps bodies that didn't make it to DN for the summon corpse thingy. While still doing a CR for some ppl our puller suddently gets assulted by Variki on his way back almost at grp. One persons takes a few steps forward to orientate hismself on what is going on (minor mistake but enough for things to go terrible wrong). Variki agros and starts ripping through our lines while the respawned adds decided to join the fun. CAMP OUT! Sounded the alarm and so we did. I and mayhaps 10 peeps more made it. Taking our time and waiting for the reentry order. When that came we all logged on and started the fight of our life. Hey we are doing great! 2 mobs one almost dead. Hmm...what is that I see out of the corner of my eye. Inc bat. Within secs 2 mobs turned to 7 mobs and we disposed heroicly of 2 of 'em and I saw peeps dropping all around me. The tactical defencive formation was falling apart and we were only 3 peeps left against 5 mobs. Not very good odds. I decided to try and pull some mobs away from the campspot and succeeded pulling away 3 of 'em. Unfortunately no where near what was needed. Death came swiftly and without merci and this time I wasn't LD so I actually experienced the pain.<br><br>Long and trivial CR again. Lots of coffins. At this point some of the peeps had been very discouraged by our failure and didn't want to continue. We quite for the day with a promise that we would come back again and be better prepared with another tactic.<br><br>And BTW doing CR is in the rat area is highly risky since rats see invis. So ye would have to fight thy way through.<br><br>Just a little story to give y'all a little insight in how tough it can be to get this.<br><br>Nerfing this weap would be in the spirit of VI but since it is highly difficult to get I gather it will not be nerfed. The no drop alteration is all in order.<br><br>Just my 2cp<br><br>I hope this info is somewhat usefull for all ye ppl that want to have a go at this.<br><br>I wish y'all happy hunting and may thy blade strike true.<br><br>Trackfinder Swifteblade member of Nordiska Kompaniet. Blessed 51 times by the fair Tunare and roaming the realm of Innoruuk.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
